        "created_at": "2024-12-28T06:53:12.964Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hello everyone,</p>\n<p>I would like to ask about the login features in Signal. If the phone number used to register has expired and cannot be accessed anymore, are there alternative methods to log in to a Signal account? For example, is it possible to log in using a registered email, Signal PIN, or any other methods?</p>\n<p>I have experienced a similar issue with another app, where all devices were suddenly logged out, and I couldnâ€™t log back in because my phone number had expired. Although I had registered an email for verification, the login page only asked for the phone number.</p>\n<p>I have been using Signal for years and want to ensure that there are other ways to log in if a similar situation occurs. This could also be a suggestion for future feature development.</p>\n<p>Thank you for your information and assistance!</p>\n<p>Best regards,</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
