        "id": 258014,
        "name": "",
        "username": "kk_007",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/3d9bf3/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2024-12-29T01:56:31.033Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hello, thank you for responding to this discussion. I understand your point, but the topic I want to highlight is different from that.</p>\n<p>I am focusing on a situation where users lose access to their phone numbers (for example, due to forgetting to renew their numberâ€™s validity or other reasons). In such cases, are there alternative login options, such as switching to login via email or using a unique identification PIN created during initial registration?</p>\n<p>In my opinion, this could be a useful additional feature. Registering with a phone number is fine, but in certain situationsâ€”such as being busy or due to oversightâ€”users might lose access to their phone numbers.</p>\n<p>For example, this happened to me on another messaging app (not Signal). I lost access to my phone number and, despite filling out the email verification form as requested, I have yet to receive a response. Unfortunately, the app did not provide an alternative login option via email, even though the email was verified during registration.</p>\n<p>I hope Signal can consider developing a similar feature in the future, so users have alternative login solutions when facing similar situations.</p>\n<p>Thank you.</p>",
        "post_number": 4,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 6,
        "updated_at": "2024-12-29T01:56:31.033Z",
        "reply_count": 1,
