        "id": 258025,
        "name": "",
        "username": "Herohtar",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/{size}/43780_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-12-29T05:02:37.252Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"kk_007\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"65737\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/k/3d9bf3/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> kk_007:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I am focusing on a situation where users lose access to their phone numbers (for example, due to forgetting to renew their numberâ€™s validity or other reasons). In such cases, are there alternative login options, such as switching to login via email or using a unique identification PIN created during initial registration?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>As I already stated, there is no alternative login. However, losing access to your phone number is not an immediate concern, as you can continue using Signal with the number, but since it is not possible to re-register using the number that you no longer have access to, you should change your Signal account number to something you <em>do</em> have access to as soon as possible.</p>",
